<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices in Australian terms are holding firm, with better styles tending
firmer and crossbreds particularly in good demand. However, weakness in the
US dollar is inevitably reflected in Australian exchange rates, and from
time to time recently Australian economic problems have tended to underline
this factor. Overseas buyers consequently find wool a little cheaper to buy.
The strength in sterling has led to more definite price reductions in the
UK. Business is at present quiet but activity in early processing remains
very good and signs of recovery from recession are cautiously indicated
elsewhere.
</TEXT>
