<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Firstland loss cut to Pounds 743,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Firstland Group, formerly Firstland Oil &amp; Gas, incurred a pre-tax loss of
Pounds 743,000 for the 1991 year.
The figure included an exceptional provision of Pounds 301,000 against a
disposal of shares in Explaura, the limestone extraction group. Losses for
the previous year amounted to Pounds 3.39m including exceptionals of Pounds
2.8m.
Turnover totalled Pounds 393,000 (Pounds 563,000) and losses per share
emerged at 3.34p (15.42p).
The group, quoted on the USM, recently announced a refinancing package and
appointed a new management team. It intends to diversify away from its oil
and gas interests and is currently looking at the areas of packaging,
distribution and specialist engineering.
</TEXT>
