FT  14 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Guinness expands in South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP RAWSTORNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Guinness has established a subsidiary in South Africa to expand its
distribution in the continent's biggest beer market.
From later this year Guinness stout will be brewed and distributed under
licence by South African Breweries.
For almost two years, limited distribution in South Africa has been handled
through Namibia Breweries, which brews and distributes the product in a
number of African markets.
Mr Alfons Walser, managing director of the new subsidiary, said yesterday:
'We believe the timing is right for us now to become directly involved in
the marketing of the Guinness brand in South Africa.'
