FT  13 MAY 92 / International Company News: UPI accepts US Media bid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BANKRUPT news agency United Press International and its creditors have
accepted a Dollars 6m cash bid by US Media, a cable TV and radio network
company controlled by television evangelist Mr Pat Robertson, Reuter
reports.
The news agency had made the bid in a US court hearing. It had been the only
offer for the news agency as a whole.
Mr Robertson said his interest in UPI included its overseas news gathering
operation and radio network, which would be 'complementary'.
US Media Corp's holdings include a cable television network.
