<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 92 / Observer: Seal of approval
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Much play is being made of the government's search for new sources of
statistics. But Observer hears that the much-maligned Central Statistical
Office has found one satisfied customer - Marks and Spencer.
Apparently, Bill McLennan, the Aussie statistician drafted in to
rehabilitate the CSO, so impressed Marks and Spencer's top brass on a recent
visit, that Britain's leading retailer has agreed to drop its participation
in a rival private scheme to collect retail information.
M and S reckons McLennan will knock the government's statistics into shape,
so there is no point in duplicating efforts and supplying data to the rival
project.
</TEXT>
