FT  13 MAY 92 / Observer: Sticky problem
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Meanwhile, in Brussels - a city already awash with lobby groups and trade
associations - it is hardly surprising that the European Association for the
Promotion of Handhygiene has so far gone unnoticed.
But the EAPH (slogan: United For Handhygiene) looks set to make a big splash
with a press conference next week, when it will reveal the results of its
inquiry into the behaviour of users of public toilets. . . .
