privatised electricity generator which owns the station.
Drax, which supplies enough power for six cities the size of Liverpool, is
on the River Ouse near British Coal's Selby colliery complex. National Power
argues that Drax could be priced out of the new electricity market if
negotiations with British Coal over coal pricing cannot be resolved.
Mr Mike Grasby, manager at Drax, warned that the station could be switched
off most of the time because of tough competition from gas-fired power
stations.
