businesses, said last month its takeover offer was conditional on it and
Hotel Properties acquiring a combined stake of more than 50 per cent. With a
50 per cent stake, CCL could wrest control of the property group from
Singapore's Teo family, which owns about 24 per cent of Malayan.
Malayan's land bank in Malaysia and its prime office and residential
properties in Singapore and Malaysia are expected to blend well with CCL's
property portfolio in Singapore and Malaysia.
