'improved enough to offset the higher costs of doing business'.
Meanwhile, May Department Stores, which operates 319 department stores
across the US under names such as Lord &amp; Taylor and Kaufmann's, and 3,304
shoe stores, reported after-tax profits of Dollars 81m for the 13 weeks to
May 2.
The result compares with Dollars 76m in the same period a year earlier.
Total net retail sales in the period were up from Dollars 2.17bn to Dollars
2.3bn.
