<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WHIRLPOOL, the largest US white goods producer, is consolidating its
presence in eastern Europe with the establishment of a joint venture with
Tatramat, the leading washing machine producer in Czechoslovakia.
The joint venture is valued at Dollars 13.7m of which Tatramat contributed
Dollars 10.7m in fixed assets and Whirlpool Dollars 3m in cash. A further
Dollars 3m was paid by Whirlpool for a second purchase of shares which
brought the group's stake to 43.8 per cent. The venture intends a further
Dollars 28m in capital expenditures over the next three or four years.
The venture will produce 400,000 washing machines by 1993 and export them to
Hungary, Poland and the former Soviet Union.
Tatramat, located in Slovakia, makes about 70 per cent of washing machines
in Czechoslovakia. Its only rival is a small Moravian company, Romo Fulnek.
